        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the {{strong-white-flour}}, {{fine-sea-salt}}, and {{instant-yeast}} in a large bowl. Add the 80 ml of {{olive-oil}} and the {{water}}. Mix until no dry flour remains, the dough will be rough and shaggy. Cover and leave for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bulk ferment with stretch and fold, 2 hours",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Perform four sets of ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "stretch and fold",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp71fvr60000z8v4inzqjasm"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " at 30-minute intervals over the first 2 hours. Between sets, cover the bowl. After the final fold, the dough should be smooth and hold its shape briefly when pulled.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Transfer and proof, 45 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour 4 tablespoons of the remaining {{olive-oil}} into a 30×40 cm tin and spread it to coat the base and sides. Tip the dough into the tin and turn it to coat in oil. Gently stretch the dough to fill the tin, do not force it; it will relax with time. Drizzle over the rest of the oil. Leave uncovered for 45 minutes until puffed.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Dimple, top, and bake, 20 to 25 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 220°C fan. With oiled fingers, press deep dimples all over the dough, push all the way to the base of the tin. Press the {{cherry-tomatoes}} and {{olives}} into the dimples. Scatter over the {{flaked-sea-salt}} and {{fresh-rosemary}} if using. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until deep golden and crisp on the base. Drizzle with a little extra olive oil as it comes out of the oven.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
